# 2. 新しい音色

Miku: Oh, you're all here. Welcome.
Saki: Hi, Miku♪ Hi, Luka♪
Luka: As peppy as ever, I see Saki.
MEIKO: Did something good happen?
Shiho: We were talking about what we should be doing if we're serious about going pro.
Shiho: And we decided to play a show at the live house I work at as part of gaining more experience as a band.
Miku: Oh, a show? That sounds fun!
Saki: I know, right?! It's time to let the world know that Leo/need has finally arrived! I can't wait!
Ichika: The world? That may be going a little too far, Saki...
Honami: But the thought of setting out into the world could give us some extra motivation.
Shiho: That also means we'll have to practice even more, you know?
Saki: Okay, we get it! This is what we chose, so we'll just have to do our best♪
Saki: That's why we're gonna need your help more than ever now, Miku. Please!
Miku: Hehe. Of course I'll help. We can practice as much as you like.
Luka: Right. We'll be more than happy to keep supporting you girls however we can.
MEIKO: Exactly! Feel free to ask us about anything you like and we'll try to help.
Honami: Thank you so much!
Shiho: Now then, how about we get started with practice.
Saki: Sounds good! Let's make today another...
Rin: Oh no! Everyone's already here?!
Rin: Talk about a late entry! MEIKO, why didn't you tell me about what was going on?!
MEIKO: Haha. I'm sorry, Rin. You were sound asleep and I didn't want to disturb you.
Ichika: What...?! Rin?!
Rin: You're the ones who created this SEKAI, right? It's nice to finally meet you!
Rin: I'm Kagamine Rin♪ I'll be a part of Miku-P's band from now on!
Rin: I'm looking forward to working with all of you☆
Shiho: Miku-P...?
Miku: *Grumble*
Luka: What a cute nickname.
Rin: See? It's so much cuter and easier than just calling you by your regular name♪
Rin: So if you don't mind, I'll be doing the same for all of you too♪ Sakki, Ichi, Hona and Shihoppy!
Ichika: Uh, okay. Thank you...
Ichika: Hold on...
Shiho: Shihoppy...?
Honami: H-Hehe. Oh no... She did it to your name too, Shiho... Hehehe...
Shiho: Honami...
Miku: Thank goodness. At least we have each other, Shiho...
Shiho: Sorry, but can you give me a different nickname?
Rin: What?! Why?! It's so cute!
Shiho: No, it's not. I'm certain that Saki's gonna start copying you too.
Saki: But your name sounds so much cuter that way...
Rin: Yeah, I'm with her♪
Shiho: Please, Rin, can't you think of something else...?
Rin: You want me to change it that badly...?
Rin: Hmm... What about Shih? Yeah! How does that sound?!
Shiho: Fine... It's better than before...
Rin: Yay! Thanks, Shih♪
MEIKO: Haha. Sorry, Miku-P. Looks like you're all alone now.
Miku: *Grumble*
Saki: Things are gonna be so much more fun now that Rin's here with us♪
Ichika: Yes, I think so too.
Honami: But that reminds me. When you came here, MEIKO, you mentioned something about our feelings moving forward.
Honami: Does that mean you're here because of the same reason, Rin?
Rin: The reason I came to this SEKAI?
Rin: I'm not really sure... When I realized it, I was here so...
Miku: It may be because you all decided to “go pro” together and gave yourselves a new challenge to face, no...?
Rin: Yeah, I think she's right! I want to help you just like Miku-P and Luka do!
Luka: They even mentioned that they'll be performing in a show. You seem to have arrived just at the right time.
Rin: What? You're gonna put on a show?!
Ichika: Yes, we are. Well, we just decided to just a little while ago.
Rin: That's so cool! Have you already decided on what you're gonna play?
Honami: No, not quite...
Rin: Oh, really?
Shiho: We don't know what we'll be playing yet, but we at least know what we want to do...
Shiho: Our goal is to play music that can move the hearts of those who come and listen to it.
Saki: Shiho...!
Rin: That's so nice! Pure friendship! I can tell how committed you are to each other!
Rin: Don't forget to ask if you ever need any help too! I'll do whatever I can to make sure your show's as happy and fun as it can be♪
Honami: Thank you, Rin.
Ichika: Then let's start practicing for it.
Saki: Yeah! Let's make today another good one!
Saki: Wow... I'm beat...
Ichika: But we have to be able to do better than this if we're serious about becoming professionals.
Ichika: How did my singing sound just now, Shiho?
Shiho: You sounded good. And you'll sound even better once you're pitch-perfect throughout the chorus.
Ichika: Okay... Got it. Thanks.
Honami: Shiho, can you do me next?
Saki: Yeah, me too!
Shiho: You have such a steady beat now, Honami, but your rimshots during the second verse were a little weak. Your rhythm is fine, so just hit it like you mean it.
Honami: Oh, that's exactly the part I was worried about. Thank you, Shiho.
Shiho: And Saki...
Shiho: Your fingers aren't keeping up during some key changes and you have a tendency to go a little too fast, so you might want to work on your finger rolls.
Saki: B-But I'm so bad at that part...
Saki: I practiced so much and still haven't gotten it down...
Shiho: You're playing the part before your synth solo much better now, so try to keep in mind what you've been doing there.
Saki: Okay! Let me write that down... The part before my solo... Got it!
Shiho: But you've all improved so much compared to before. Let's keep this up and get ready for our show.
Saki: ...
Saki: (*Sigh*... I still have so much work to do...)
Saki: (I wasn't able to play the piano for so long since I was in the hospital. Am I holding everyone back...?)
Saki: (No, I don't have time for any of that. I need to keep practicing...!)
